---
import PublicLayout from '@layouts/PublicLayout.astro';
---

<PublicLayout
  title="About"
  description="Learn about the history and formation of St. Teresa of Kolkata Church, Paldane."
>
  <!-- HERO -->
  <section
    class="relative min-h-[55vh] flex items-center justify-center overflow-hidden pt-24"
  >
    <!-- Premium gradient background (temporary until photos are added) -->
    <div
      class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-charcoal-950 via-charcoal-900 to-primary-900"
    ></div>

    <!-- Soft overlay -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-black/35"></div>

    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-5xl px-6 text-center">
      <h1 class="font-serif text-5xl md:text-7xl font-bold text-white mb-6">
        About Our Parish
      </h1>

      <div class="w-24 h-[2px] bg-white mx-auto mb-6 rounded-full"></div>

      <p
        class="text-white/85 text-lg md:text-xl leading-relaxed max-w-3xl mx-auto"
      >
        St. Teresa of Kolkata Church, Paldane is a vibrant Catholic community built
        through faith, sacrifice, and the unity of parishioners.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- MAIN CONTENT -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-6xl">
      <!-- INTRO -->
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center mb-16">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-bold text-charcoal-900 mb-4">
          Formation of Paldane Parish
        </h2>
        <p class="text-charcoal-700 text-lg leading-relaxed">
          Our parish was formed with the vision of bringing the faithful closer to God,
          ensuring spiritual care for Catholic families in and around Paldane.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- HISTORY CARDS -->
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-10 max-w-6xl mx-auto">
        <div class="rounded-3xl border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 p-10 shadow-sm">
          <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-charcoal-900 mb-4">
            Foundation & Land Purchase (2004)
          </h3>

          <p class="text-charcoal-700 leading-relaxed text-lg">
            After consulting the finance committee, Gurkars, ward representatives, and
            parishioners, the Cordel Parish leadership proposed the establishment of a new
            church at Paldane to serve Catholic families nearby.
          </p>

          <p class="text-charcoal-700 leading-relaxed text-lg mt-5">
            With support from parishioners and donors, around one and a half acres of land
            was purchased and registered on <strong>19th March 2004</strong>.
            On the same day, the foundation stone was laid by
            <strong>Bishop Aloysius Paul D'Souza</strong>.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-3xl border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 p-10 shadow-sm">
          <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-charcoal-900 mb-4">
            Dedication to Blessed Teresa of Kolkata
          </h3>

          <p class="text-charcoal-700 leading-relaxed text-lg">
            As per the wish of the people, the church was dedicated to
            <strong>Blessed Teresa of Kolkata</strong>, who was declared Blessed on
            <strong>19-10-2003</strong>.
          </p>

          <p class="text-charcoal-700 leading-relaxed text-lg mt-5">
            Construction work was entrusted to <strong>Roy Construction</strong>, and
            electrical works were completed by
            <strong>Mr. William Fernandes (Royal Electrical)</strong>.
            The project was completed with cooperation from Cordel Church,
            parishioners, and generous donors.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- TIMELINE -->
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto mt-20">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-bold text-charcoal-900 text-center mb-12">
          Parish Timeline
        </h2>

        <div class="space-y-10">
          <div class="flex gap-6 items-start">
            <div class="flex flex-col items-center">
              <div class="w-4 h-4 bg-primary-600 rounded-full"></div>
              <div class="w-[2px] bg-gray-300 flex-1 mt-2"></div>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-3xl p-8 shadow-sm w-full">
              <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-charcoal-900 mb-2">
                22nd April 2006 – Grand Preparations
              </h3>
              <p class="text-charcoal-700 text-lg leading-relaxed">
                A grand pendol was arranged to accommodate nearly 4000 people.
                Multiple committees were formed to ensure smooth celebration.
                A motorcade procession was held to bring food supplies, with nearly 1000 participants.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-6 items-start">
            <div class="flex flex-col items-center">
              <div class="w-4 h-4 bg-primary-600 rounded-full"></div>
              <div class="w-[2px] bg-gray-300 flex-1 mt-2"></div>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-3xl p-8 shadow-sm w-full">
              <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-charcoal-900 mb-2">
                24th April 2006 – Inauguration
              </h3>
              <p class="text-charcoal-700 text-lg leading-relaxed">
                The Presbytery was inaugurated by <strong>Very Rev. Fr. G.W. Vas</strong>.
                The Church was blessed and inaugurated by
                <strong>Bishop Aloysius Paul D'Souza</strong>, followed by a thanksgiving Mass
                with many diocesan and religious priests.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-6 items-start">
            <div class="flex flex-col items-center">
              <div class="w-4 h-4 bg-primary-600 rounded-full"></div>
              <div class="w-[2px] bg-gray-300 flex-1 mt-2"></div>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-3xl p-8 shadow-sm w-full">
              <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-charcoal-900 mb-2">
                13th August 2006 – Parish Declared Independent
              </h3>
              <p class="text-charcoal-700 text-lg leading-relaxed">
                A decree was issued on <strong>16th July 2006</strong>, declaring Paldane Church
                an independent parish effective from <strong>13-08-2006</strong>.
                At the time, the parish consisted of around <strong>250 Catholic families</strong>.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-6 items-start">
            <div class="flex flex-col items-center">
              <div class="w-4 h-4 bg-primary-600 rounded-full"></div>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-3xl p-8 shadow-sm w-full">
              <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-charcoal-900 mb-2">
                Today – A Growing Faith Community
              </h3>
              <p class="text-charcoal-700 text-lg leading-relaxed">
                Today, St. Teresa of Kolkata Church continues to grow as a parish rooted in
                devotion, catechism, and parish unity serving the faithful of Paldane with love.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- PRIESTS SECTION -->
      <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto mt-24">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-bold text-charcoal-900 text-center mb-6">
          Parish Priests Who Served
        </h2>
        <p class="text-center text-charcoal-700 text-lg mb-14">
          Dedicated priests who guided our parish community through the years.
        </p>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-8">
          <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-3xl p-6 shadow-sm">
            <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-bold text-charcoal-900 mb-2">
              Fr Gregory W. Vas
            </h3>
            <p class="text-charcoal-700">2006 – 2016</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-3xl p-6 shadow-sm">
            <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-bold text-charcoal-900 mb-2">
              Fr Vincent V. Menezes
            </h3>
            <p class="text-charcoal-700">2016 – 2019</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-3xl p-6 shadow-sm">
            <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-bold text-charcoal-900 mb-2">
              Fr Alban D'Souza
            </h3>
            <p class="text-charcoal-700">2019 – 2025</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-3xl p-6 shadow-sm">
            <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-bold text-charcoal-900 mb-2">
              Rev. Fr Richard Aloysius Coelho
            </h3>
            <p class="text-charcoal-700">2025 – Present</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- QUICK FACTS -->
      <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto mt-24">
        <div class="rounded-3xl border border-gray-200 bg-white p-10 shadow-sm">
          <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl font-bold text-charcoal-900 mb-6">
            Parish Highlights
          </h2>

          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
            <div>
              <p class="text-sm text-charcoal-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">
                Parish Established
              </p>
              <p class="text-xl font-semibold text-charcoal-900">
                13th August 2006
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <p class="text-sm text-charcoal-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">
                Dedication
              </p>
              <p class="text-xl font-semibold text-charcoal-900">
                St. Teresa of Kolkata
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <p class="text-sm text-charcoal-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">
                Diocese
              </p>
              <p class="text-xl font-semibold text-charcoal-900">
                Diocese of Mangalore
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</PublicLayout>
